oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Songwriter Session - Kelly Archer - 2017-10-28
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by singer songwriter Kelly Archer from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on October 28, 2017. Includes questions from the audience.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Kelly Archer;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) Introductory comments by Abi Tapia begin in progress / (01:20) Opening comments by Kelly and talks about her background / (04:18) Introduces the next song / (04:56) Performs Somebody Else Will / (07:55) Welcomes audience members / (08:48) Talks about story songs in country music and introduces the next song / (10:14) Performs Something Borrowed / (14:28) Talks about Justin Moore and co-writing songs with Justin Weaver and tells story of being let go from her publishing deal / (17:49) Performs On My Highway / (21:54) Introduces the next song / (25:30) Performs For Her / (29:25) Talks about writing the next song / (33:) Performs Love Like Mine / (36:17) Talks about the next song / (36:59) Performs unidentified song probably titled I'm Gonna Love You / (39:56) Answers question from the audience about co-writing and the ideas for songs / (43:05) Performs Sleep Without You / (46:07) Final comments / (46:31) Walk-our music / (49:40) FILE END
